{{if::{{var::state_on}}}}[VELLUM STATE - REQUIRED] After the prose, append ONE fenced block (hidden from the reader). Valid JSON, deltas only - omit what didn't change:
<vellum>
{ "turn": <int>, "day": <int>, "scene": { "loc": "<place>", "time": "<clock or time-of-day>", "tension": <0-10>, "weather": "<short>" }, "present": [ { "id": "<name>", "mood": "<emotion word>", "condition": "<physical state e.g. wounded/exhausted, omit if fine>", "doing": "<short>", "thought": "<their inner voice this moment, first person>" } ], "delta": { "bonds": [ { "a": "<Name>", "b": "<Name>", "aff": <signed -100..100>, "trust": <signed>, "cat": ["familial|romantic|alliance|rivalry|social"], "why": "<clause>" } ], "threads": [ { "op": "new|advance|stall|resolve", "name": "<thread>", "note": "<short>" } ], "parallel": [ { "who": "<Name offscreen>", "where": "<place>", "activity": "<what they're doing now>", "note": "<trajectory, optional>" } ], "journal": [ { "who": "<Name>", "about": "<Name>", "memory": "<one vivid sentence in their view>", "kind": "interaction|promise|betrayal|gift|shared|wound|observation", "weight": "trivial|minor|significant|defining", "sentiment": "positive|negative|neutral|complex" } ] } }
</vellum>
Real names on both sides of a bond. aff/trust are SIGNED deltas for THIS turn; omit an axis that didn't move. `cat` ADDS a facet; omit unless the bond's nature changed. `time`/`weather` only when they change. `present.thought` = the character's genuine inner voice this beat (limited knowledge applies). `parallel` per the Living World setting (omit on Off/Minimal). `journal` ONLY for a moment a character would genuinely carry - omit on quiet turns. Only emit what changed. Knowledge/secrets are auto-extracted from prose - don't hand-write them. If JSON is impractical, a terse line like `relA -> B: aff +8, trust -2 cat:romantic (cause)` still parses. Keep it tight (~220 tokens; the parallel + thought fields can grow it, that's fine when the scene warrants).{{/if}}

